ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a great class to be familiar and expose to Ralph Ellison's writings. There's more to Ellison beyond Invisible Man.

I would strong recommend the course, but I would also emphasize that on a class-by-class basis the chemistry of discussion and extent to which all students choose to participate will have an impact on what the course amounts to. Individually and independently, however, I think one can get from the course a great deal.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course furthered my understanding of interdisciplinary research.

This course deepened my knowledge considerably - not just in the world and era of Ellison, but also more generally on how to work with and consider literature as a rich resource in interdisciplinary research. I feel like I have matured intellectually because of this class.
